&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: A minimum of a Bachelor’s degree from an accredited institution in History, Geography, Library Science, Museum Studies, Museum Science, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: A minimum of 8 years of hands-on experience in the career field of history, geography, library science, museum studies, or museum science role.&amp;nbsp; In lieu of a bachelor’s degree, the candidate must have 8+ years of direct museum practice, artifact preservation, curation, or history-related positions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication Skills: Strong written and verbal communication abilities with an eagerness to draft, edit, and proofread materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to Detail: A high degree of accuracy and thoroughness when completing tasks such as inventorying and entering records metadata, or recording the origins and significance of archival materials.&lt;/li&gt;
